    - name: Grain
      style: Float
      default: 1
      max: 2.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 2.0
    - name: Vignette
      style: Float
      default: 0.7
      max: 1.5
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 1.5
  position: [1200, 0]
  tdn_ref: specimen_lab/hyper_ntsc.tdn
- name: murmuration
  type: baseCOMP
  custom_pars:
    Murmuration:
    - name: Cohesion
      style: Float
      startSection: true
      default: 0.04
      max: 2.0
      clampMin: true
      normMax: 0.5
      help: Steer toward the local flock centroid (Reynolds cohesion).
    - name: Alignment
      style: Float
      default: 0.55
      max: 3.0
      clampMin: true
      normMax: 2.0
      help: Match the mean heading of neighbors (Reynolds alignment).
    - name: Separation
      style: Float
      default: 0.9
      max: 5.0
      clampMin: true
      normMax: 3.0
      help: Inverse-square repulsion from close neighbors. Prevents collapse - the anti-blob force.
    - name: Attractor
      style: Float
      default: 0.15
      max: 2.0
      clampMin: true
      help: Pull toward the slow wandering roost attractor.
    - name: Spiral
      style: Float
      default: 0.55
      max: 3.0
      clampMin: true
      normMax: 2.0
      help: Tangential swirl around the attractor (vortex shear / split-reform).
    - name: Curl
      style: Float
      default: 0.4
      max: 3.0
      clampMin: true
      normMax: 2.0
      help: Curl-noise wander for organic break-up.
    - name: Bodyradius
      style: Float
      label: Body Radius
      startSection: true
      default: 2.4
      min: 0.5
      max: 6.0
      clampMin: true
      normMin: 1.0
      normMax: 4.0
      help: Soft containment radius - the size of the coherent body.
    - name: Morphspeed
      style: Float
      label: Morph Speed
      default: 1
      max: 4.0
      clampMin: true
      normMax: 3.0
      help: Overall evolution rate (attractor drift + curl). 0 freezes the motion.
    - name: Maxparticles
      style: Int
      label: Max Particles
      startSection: true
      default: 5000
      min: 100.0
      clampMin: true
      normMin: 1000.0
      normMax: 40000.0
      help: Maximum live particle pool.
    - name: Birthrate
      style: Float
      label: Birth Rate
      default: 2000
      clampMin: true
      normMax: 8000.0
      help: Particles born per second.
    Output:
      $t: output_2
  position: [0, -800]
  tdn_ref: specimen_lab/murmuration.tdn
- name: kaleidoscope
  type: baseCOMP
  custom_pars:
    Kaleidoscope:
    - name: Segments
      style: Int
      startSection: true
      default: 8
      min: 2.0
      max: 24.0
      clampMin: true
      normMin: 2.0
      normMax: 16.0
      help: Number of mirror wedges around the center. Higher = more intricate symmetry.
    - name: Rotation
      style: Float
      normMin: -3.1416
      normMax: 3.1416
      help: Base rotation of the mirror, in radians. The animation rotates on top of this.
    - name: Zoom
      style: Float
      default: 1
      min: 0.1
      clampMin: true
      normMin: 0.3
      normMax: 3.0
      help: How much of the source each wedge samples. Higher = more facets packed in.
    - name: Flowspeed
      style: Float
      label: Flow Speed
      default: 1
      clampMin: true
      normMax: 3.0
      help: Speed of the tumble / twist / rotation animation. 0 freezes it.
    - name: Palette
      style: Float
      label: Palette Hue
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      help: Rotates the color palette through the full hue range. 0 = fiery.
    - name: Source
      style: Menu
      startSection: true
      default: demo
      menuNames:
      - demo
      - external
      menuLabels:
      - Demo (built-in)
      - External input
      help: Demo = built-in animated source. External = kaleidoscope whatever TOP is wired into this COMP.
    Output:
      $t: output
  position: [800, -400]
  tdn_ref: specimen_lab/kaleidoscope.tdn
- name: noise_terrain
  type: baseCOMP
  custom_pars:
    Terrain:
    - name: Height
      style: Float
      startSection: true
      default: 1
      max: 2.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 2.0
      help: Overall vertical scale of the terrain. Master multiplier on all three noise displacement amplitudes, preserving their 2.9 / 1.0 / 0.25 ratio so peaks and fine relief grow in proportion. 1.0 = the shipped look; 0 = a flat plane; 2 = double-height alpine peaks.
    - name: Ridge
      style: Float
      default: 1.6
      min: 1.0
      max: 3.0
      clampMin: true
      normMin: 1.0
      normMax: 3.0
      help: Ridge sharpness of the mountains. Higher values carve sharper, more knife-edged ridgelines and deeper valleys; lower values give rounder, more eroded hills. 1.6 = the shipped look.
    - name: Warp
      style: Float
      default: 1.2
      max: 2.5
      clampMin: true
      normMax: 2.5
      help: Domain warp amount. Bends the noise domain so ridgelines flow organically instead of aligning to a grid. 0 = regular and repetitive; 1.2 = the shipped look; higher = more chaotic, swirling ridges.
    - name: Detail
      style: Float
      default: 1
      max: 2.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 2.0
      help: Surface micro-detail and ruggedness, applied cheaply in the shader as normal-map bump strength (no mesh change, so no triangulation cost or facet artifacts). Scales the shipped bump strength of 0.17. 1.0 = the shipped look; 0 = smooth shading; 2 = heavily rugged rock.
    - name: Snowline
      style: Float
      label: Snow Line
      startSection: true
      default: 1.6
      max: 4.0
      clampMin: true
      normMax: 4.0
      help: World-Y elevation where snow begins to cover the rock. Peaks reach roughly 0 to 4 at Height 1.0, so 1.6 sits mid-slope (the shipped look). Lower the value to blanket the terrain in snow; the slider covers 0 to 4, but you can type higher to clear taller peaks at high Height, leaving only bare rock.
    - name: Sundiraz
      style: Float
      label: Sun Azimuth
      startSection: true
      default: -41.6335
      min: -180.0
      max: 180.0
      normMin: -180.0
      normMax: 180.0
      help: Compass direction of the sunlight, in degrees in the horizontal plane. 0 points toward +Z (into the scene), +90 toward +X (right), -90 toward -X (left). Combined with Sun Elevation it is converted to a guaranteed unit light direction, so it can never produce a zero-length (NaN) vector. Controls which side of the ridges is lit.
    - name: Sundirel
      style: Float
      label: Sun Elevation
      default: 49.3007
      max: 90.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 90.0
      help: Height of the sun above the horizon, in degrees. 0 = sun on the horizon (long raking shadows, warm grazing light); 90 = directly overhead (flat, even light). Controls shadow length and contrast. The default matches the shipped sun direction.
    - name: Haze
      style: Float
      startSection: true
      default: 1
      max: 2.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 2.0
      help: Atmospheric haze amount, a multiplier on the computed distance fog and valley mist. 0 = perfectly clear air; 1.0 = the shipped atmosphere; up to 2 = thick, hazy depth that washes out distant peaks. The blend is re-clamped in the shader so it can never fully erase the scene.
    - name: Morphspeed
      style: Float
      label: Morph Speed
      startSection: true
      default: 1
      max: 3.0
      clampMin: true
      normMax: 3.0
      help: Rate at which the terrain shape evolves over time, driving the 4D-noise time coordinate of all three layers while preserving their 0.04 / 0.085 / 0.15 speed ratio. 0 = frozen on a fixed, deterministic frame; 1.0 = the shipped pace; 3 = rapid morphing.
    - name: Seed
      style: Int
      startSection: true
      default: 1
      max: 9999.0
      clampMin: true
      normMax: 100.0
      help: Random seed for the terrain shape. Each value produces a completely different but equally plausible mountain. The three noise layers receive this value plus a fixed per-layer offset (+0, +1, +2) so they stay decorrelated. Default 1 reproduces the shipped seeds 1 / 2 / 3.
    Output:
      $t: output_2
  position: [400, -800]
  tdn_ref: specimen_lab/noise_terrain.tdn
- name: packet_fabric
  type: baseCOMP
  custom_pars:
    Controls:
    - name: Maxpackets
      style: Int
      default: 5000
      min: 200.0
      max: 16000.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 200.0
      normMax: 16000.0
      help: how many packets cascade down the fabric. Cost scales with this (GPU), NOT with output resolution, so it is independent of the 4K story. Watch GPU headroom; cap 16000.
    - name: Flowspeed
      style: Float
      default: 0.45
      max: 1.5
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 1.5
      help: how fast packets descend each link per second. 0 freezes the cascade (drops time-dependence); higher = near-light-speed rain.
    - name: Linkcount
      style: Int
      default: 26
      min: 4.0
      max: 64.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 4.0
      normMax: 64.0
      help: number of distinct sender->receiver vertical links. More = a busier topology.
    - name: Curveamount
      style: Float
      default: 1
      max: 2.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 2.0
      help: how much each vertical link bows horizontally (fiber slack). 0 = straight drops; higher = graceful arcs.
    - name: Streams
      style: Int
      default: 3
      min: 1.0
      max: 3.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 1.0
      normMax: 3.0
      help: number of separated ST2110 essence classes (1=video, 2=+audio, 3=+ancillary). Colors packets cyan/green/amber by PartId class.
    - name: Ptprate
      style: Float
      default: 0.5
      min: 0.1
      max: 2.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 0.1
      normMax: 2.0
      help: frequency of the PTP grandmaster sync pulse all packets flash to in lockstep. The rhythmic heartbeat.
    - name: Pulsestrength
      style: Float
      default: 1.4
      max: 3.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 3.0
      help: how brightly packets flash on each PTP beat. 0 = steady cascade; higher = a dramatic synchronized strobe.
    - name: Fieldscale
      style: Float
      default: 1.35
      min: 0.5
      max: 2.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 0.5
      normMax: 2.0
      help: spread of node anchors across the tall field. Higher = a wider, more sprawling fabric.
    - name: Jitter
      style: Float
      default: 1
      max: 2.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 2.0
      help: tiny per-packet phase stagger so the cascade looks like real quantized traffic, not a marching grid. 0 = perfectly synced ranks.
    - name: Bloom
      style: Float
      default: 1.3
      max: 3.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 3.0
      help: intensity of the bright-pass glow added back. The booth-scale wow knob.
    - name: Bloomwidth
      style: Float
      default: 2.2
      min: 1.0
      max: 4.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 1.0
      normMax: 4.0
      help: blur step in the 1/4-res bloom pass. Wider = a softer halo, still cheap (low-res).
    Output:
    - name: Resw
      style: Int
      default: 3840
      min: 256.0
      max: 7680.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 256.0
      normMax: 7680.0
    - name: Resh
      style: Int
      default: 2160
      min: 256.0
      max: 7680.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 256.0
      normMax: 7680.0
  position: [400, -400]
  tdn_ref: specimen_lab/packet_fabric.tdn
- name: waveform_stack
  type: baseCOMP
  custom_pars:
    Output:
    - name: Resw
      style: Int
      default: 3840
      min: 256.0
      max: 7680.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 256.0
      normMax: 7680.0
      help: Render width (px), 4K landscape.
    - name: Resh
      style: Int
      default: 2160
      min: 256.0
      max: 7680.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 256.0
      normMax: 7680.0
      help: Render height (px), 4K landscape.
    Controls:
    - name: Lanes
      style: Int
      default: 96
      min: 1.0
      max: 512.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 1.0
      normMax: 512.0
      help: number of vertically-stacked scope lanes (1=green audio only; more add cyan video, magenta chroma, amber...). The ST2110 separated essences, one lane each. The row-fold costs nothing per pixel regardl
    - name: Frequency
      style: Float
      default: 8
      min: 1.0
      max: 30.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 1.0
      normMax: 30.0
      help: base spatial frequency of the waveforms. Low = slow rolling signal; high = dense rapid oscillation across the lane.
    - name: Amplitude
      style: Float
      default: 1
      max: 2.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 2.0
      help: vertical swing of each trace within its lane. 0 = flat baselines; higher = tall dramatic waveforms (clamped to stay in-lane).
    - name: Speed
      style: Float
      default: 1
      max: 4.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 4.0
      help: how fast the waveform content evolves. 0 freezes the shape (the sweep still moves).
    - name: Sweeprate
      style: Float
      default: 0.4
      min: 0.05
      max: 2.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 0.05
      normMax: 2.0
      help: how fast the white-hot playhead sweeps left-to-right across all lanes (Hz). The scope refresh feel.
    - name: Afterglow
      style: Float
      default: 0.85
      min: 0.5
      max: 0.97
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 0.5
      normMax: 0.97
      help: uSweep.y (in-shader persistence) AND level_decay.opacity (the low-res Feedback TOP decay). Higher = a longer CRT phosphor tail. Below 1 keeps the feedback bounded.
    - name: Linewidth
      style: Float
      default: 0.006
      min: 0.002
      max: 0.02
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 0.002
      normMax: 0.02
      help: thickness of the trace core (within-lane UV). Thin = a crisp precise scope line; thicker = a heavier glowing beam. Crisp at any res via fwidth().
    - name: Graticule
      style: Float
      default: 1
      max: 2.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 2.0
      help: brightness of the gold graticule grid + lane dividers. 0 hides the grid; higher makes the engineering scope frame prominent.
    - name: Harmonics
      style: Float
      default: 1
      max: 2.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 2.0
      help: amount of high harmonic detail in the signal. 0 = a clean fundamental sine; higher = a rich complex broadcast waveform.
    - name: Glow
      style: Float
      default: 1
      max: 2.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 2.0
      help: width of the soft halo around each trace before bloom. The signature scope-beam glow.
    - name: Ptprate
      style: Float
      default: 0.5
      min: 0.1
      max: 2.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 0.1
      normMax: 2.0
      help: frequency of the PTP sync pulse the whole stack breathes to.
    - name: Bloom
      style: Float
      default: 1.2
      max: 3.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 3.0
      help: intensity of the bloom added back. The booth-scale glow knob.
    - name: Bloomwidth
      style: Float
      default: 2.2
      min: 1.0
      max: 4.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 1.0
      normMax: 4.0
      help: blur step in the 1/4-res bloom pass. Wider = a softer halo, still cheap (low-res).
    - name: Scanlines
      style: Float
      default: 0.6
      max: 1.5
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 1.5
      help: strength of the CRT scanline overlay in the finish pass. 0 = clean digital; higher = a heavier broadcast-CRT texture.
    - name: Rgbsplit
      style: Float
      default: 1
      max: 2.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 2.0
      help: strength of the chromatic RGB separation event pulsed on the PTP beat. 0 = clean; higher = a pronounced broadcast chroma tear at each tick.
  position: [0, -400]
  tdn_ref: specimen_lab/waveform_stack.tdn
