- name: vertical_fibers
  type: baseCOMP
  custom_pars:
    Controls:
    - name: Strands
      style: Int
      default: 56
      min: 4.0
      max: 320.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 4.0
      normMax: 320.0
      help: number of fiber strands in the curtain. Because of the column-fold this costs NOTHING per pixel (no strand loop), so a dense premium bundle is free; raise it freely for a fuller curtain.
    - name: Converge
      style: Float
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      help: how strongly the bundle narrows toward the top. 0 = parallel strands (a flat curtain); higher = strong upward perspective into the haze.
    - name: Bow
      style: Float
      default: 1
      max: 2.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 2.0
      help: amount of gentle per-strand bow so the strands read as relaxed cable, not laser-straight. 0 = dead-straight fibers.
    - name: Glassglow
      style: Float
      default: 1.15
      max: 6.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 6.0
      help: strength of the internal-reflection shimmer gradient along each glass tube. The light-bouncing-in-glass look.
    - name: Pulsespeed
      style: Float
      default: 0.6
      max: 2.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 2.0
      help: how fast the light pulses race UP the strands. 0 freezes them (and drops that time-dependence); higher = near-light-speed streaks.
    - name: Pulsedensity
      style: Int
      default: 4
      min: 1.0
      max: 4.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 1.0
      normMax: 4.0
      help: how many light pulses travel up each strand at once (1-4, the constant loop bound). More = a busier data stream.
    - name: Pulselength
      style: Float
      default: 0.32
      min: 0.02
      max: 0.5
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 0.02
      normMax: 0.5
      help: length of each Gaussian light dash (in vertical UV). Short = crisp countable packets; long = streaking light trails.
    - name: Haze
      style: Float
      default: 2.6
      max: 4.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 4.0
      help: volumetric haze building toward the top of the frame so distant strands dim into fog. Adds vertical depth.
    - name: Linewidth
      style: Float
      default: 0.0045
      min: 0.0012
      max: 0.02
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 0.0012
      normMax: 0.02
      help: base thickness of the glass tube core. Thin = crisp hairline fibers; thicker = heavier glowing tubes. Crisp at any resolution via fwidth().
    - name: Ptprate
      style: Float
      default: 0.5
      min: 0.1
      max: 2.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 0.1
      normMax: 2.0
      help: frequency of the PTP sync pulse all light pulses breathe brighter to in lockstep.
    - name: Bloom
      style: Float
      default: 0.55
      max: 3.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 3.0
      help: intensity of the downsampled bloom glow added back over the pulses. The booth-scale wow knob.
    - name: Bloomwidth
      style: Float
      default: 2.6
      min: 1.0
      max: 4.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 1.0
      normMax: 4.0
      help: the blur step in the 1/4-res bloom pass. Wider = a softer, more atmospheric glow halo (still cheap, since it runs at low res).
    - name: Grain
      style: Float
      default: 1
      max: 2.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 2.0
      help: film-grain amount in the finish pass. Kills banding on the dark gradient at large scale.
    - name: Vignette
      style: Float
      default: 0.95
      max: 1.5
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 1.5
      help: edge darkening so the curtain sits on a premium dark stage.
    Output:
      $t: output
  position: [400, 0]
  tdn_ref: specimen_lab/vertical_fibers.tdn
- name: mandelbulb_march
  type: baseCOMP
  custom_pars:
    Mandelbulb:
    - name: Power
      style: Float
      startSection: true
      default: 8
      min: 2.0
      max: 12.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 2.0
      normMax: 12.0
      help: Mandelbulb exponent in z=z^Power+c. 8 is the classic bulb; 2-4 = blobby organic forms; 10-12 = more lobes and finer detail.
    - name: Detail
      style: Float
      label: Surface Detail
      default: 0.6
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      help: Raymarch hit threshold, remapped to a 0.0015->0.0004 epsilon. Higher resolves finer fractal crenellation at more cost near grazing rays.
    - name: Glow
      style: Float
      default: 1
      max: 3.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 3.0
      help: Proximity/iteration glow added along every ray. Close-but-miss rays accumulate an exponential halo. 0 = matte; 3 = ethereal bloom.
    - name: Orbitspeed
      style: Float
      label: Orbit Speed
      startSection: true
      default: 1
      max: 3.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 3.0
      help: Multiplies absTime.seconds into the camera orbit. 0 freezes a still; 1 is a slow cinematic orbit. Only the camera moves -- the fractal math is identical each frame.
    - name: Hue
      style: Float
      default: 0.55
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      help: Base hue offset of the orbit-trap cosine palette. Rotates the whole color identity (surface, glow, rim, background sun) through the spectrum.
    - name: Sunazim
      style: Float
      label: Sun Azimuth
      startSection: true
      default: 35
      min: -180.0
      max: 180.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: -180.0
      normMax: 180.0
      help: Azimuth (degrees) of the key light, converted with elevation into a unit direction so normalize() never sees a zero vector. Rotates where the soft key light and shadow fall.
    - name: Sunelev
      style: Float
      label: Sun Elevation
      default: 45
      min: -10.0
      max: 90.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: -10.0
      normMax: 90.0
      help: Elevation (degrees) of the key light. High = top-down soft light with short shadows; low = dramatic raking light with long soft shadows.
    Output:
      $t: output_2
  position: [800, -800]
  tdn_ref: specimen_lab/mandelbulb_march.tdn
- name: crosspoint_matrix
  type: baseCOMP
  custom_pars:
    Matrix:
    - name: Gridsize
      style: Int
      label: Matrix Size (N)
      startSection: true
      default: 20
      min: 4.0
      max: 40.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 4.0
      normMax: 40.0
      help: NxN crosspoint matrix dimension.
    - name: Activeroutes
      style: Int
      label: Active Routes
      default: 16
      min: 1.0
      max: 20.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 1.0
      normMax: 20.0
      help: Routes lit simultaneously.
    - name: Latticeglow
      style: Float
      label: Lattice Glow
      default: 1
      max: 2.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 2.0
      help: Brightness of the dim unlit grid.
    - name: Crosspointglow
      style: Float
      label: Crosspoint Glow
      default: 1
      max: 2.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 2.0
      help: Brightness of lit crosspoints + paths.
    - name: Packetspeed
      style: Float
      label: Packet Speed
      startSection: true
      default: 0.5
      max: 2.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 2.0
      help: Speed packets race the L-path. 0 freezes.
    - name: Packetdensity
      style: Int
      label: Packet Density
      default: 8
      min: 1.0
      max: 10.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 1.0
      normMax: 10.0
      help: Packets per active route.
    - name: Streams
      style: Int
      label: Essence Streams
      default: 3
      min: 1.0
      max: 3.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 1.0
      normMax: 3.0
      help: Separated essence colors (cyan/green/amber).
    - name: Ptprate
      style: Float
      label: PTP Beat Rate
      startSection: true
      default: 0.5
      min: 0.1
      max: 2.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 0.1
      normMax: 2.0
      help: PTP sync pulse frequency.
    - name: Reconfigrate
      style: Float
      label: Reconfigure Rate
      default: 0.25
      min: 0.05
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 0.05
      help: How often active routes reconfigure.
    - name: Lockindicators
      style: Float
      label: Lock Indicators
      default: 1
      max: 2.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 2.0
      help: Corner PTP-lock dot brightness.
    - name: Bloom
      style: Float
      startSection: true
      default: 1.1
      max: 3.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 3.0
      help: Bloom over lit crosspoints + packets.
    - name: Glitch
      style: Float
      default: 0.8
      max: 2.0
      clampMin: true
      normMax: 2.0
      help: 'VHS glitch amount: chroma split, tape jitter/tear, rolling scanlines, grain.'
    Output:
      $t: output
  position: [800, 0]
  tdn_ref: specimen_lab/crosspoint_matrix.tdn
- name: reaction_diffusion
  type: baseCOMP
  custom_pars:
    Output:
    - name: Resw
      style: Int
      default: 3840
      min: 256.0
      max: 7680.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 256.0
      normMax: 7680.0
      help: Output width (px), 4K. The reaction sim stays bounded 16:9; out1 upscales to this.
    - name: Resh
      style: Int
      default: 2160
      min: 256.0
      max: 7680.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 256.0
      normMax: 7680.0
      help: Output height (px), 4K.
  position: [1200, -400]
  tdn_ref: specimen_lab/reaction_diffusion.tdn
- name: plasma_interference
  type: baseCOMP
  custom_pars:
    Plasma:
    - name: Scale
      style: Float
      startSection: true
      default: 6
      min: 1.0
      max: 20.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMin: 1.0
      normMax: 20.0
      help: Spatial frequency of the sine fields. Low = broad lava-lamp blobs; high = dense fine plasma.
    - name: Speed
      style: Float
      default: 1
      max: 4.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 4.0
      help: Animation speed. 1 = gentle flow; 0 freezes a still (the TOP keeps cooking, frame is identical).
    - name: Warp
      style: Float
      default: 1.2
      max: 3.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 3.0
      help: Domain-warp amount. 0 = flat sliding stripes; higher bends the coords into a flowing liquid swirl.
    - name: Complexity
      style: Float
      label: Interference
      default: 1
      max: 2.0
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      normMax: 2.0
      help: Detune between the two sine fields. 0 = one clean plasma; higher beats them into shimmering moire.
    - name: Palette
      style: Float
      label: Palette Hue
      startSection: true
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      help: Rotates the cyclic cosine palette through the full hue ring. Loops seamlessly 1.0 -> 0.0.
    - name: Contrast
      style: Float
      default: 0.4
      clampMin: true
      clampMax: true
      help: Palette saturation/contrast (onto a 0.6 base in the shader). Low = pastel; high = punchy neon.
    Output:
      $t: output_2
  position: [1200, -800]
  tdn_ref: specimen_lab/plasma_interference.tdn
